WEBVTT

00:01.034 --> 00:01.867
(BARNEY EXCLAIMING)

00:01.869 --> 00:04.236
Lily, I heard this
great joke at work
today.

00:04.238 --> 00:06.138
Dude, come on.
She's not gonna like it.

00:06.140 --> 00:08.073
It's boy-funny.
It's not girl-funny.

00:08.075 --> 00:12.144
That is sexist!
Funny is funny,
Ted.

00:12.146 --> 00:13.912
Lily's cool.
She'll appreciate this.

00:13.914 --> 00:15.681
You're on your own, man.

00:15.683 --> 00:17.816
Just tell me the joke.

00:17.818 --> 00:18.584
Okay. Ready?

00:18.586 --> 00:23.756
Lily, what's the difference
between peanut butter and
jam?

00:23.758 --> 00:24.923
(SNICKERING)

00:24.925 --> 00:26.492
See? It's funny.
It's boy-funny.

00:26.494 --> 00:27.559
She's not gonna like it.

00:27.561 --> 00:29.261
Why don't you
let me decide?

00:29.263 --> 00:30.329
(EXCLAIMING)

00:30.331 --> 00:33.532
What's the difference
between peanut butter
and jam?

00:34.601 --> 00:36.468
<i>OLDER TED:</i>
<i>And then Barney</i>
<i>said the punch line.</i>

00:36.470 --> 00:40.806
<i>To this day, it's</i>
<i>still the dirtiest joke</i>
<i>I've ever heard in my life.</i>

00:40.808 --> 00:42.775
<i>And no,</i>
<i>I'm not gonna say it.</i>

00:43.576 --> 00:46.812
Yeah, I can't hang
out with you anymore.

00:46.814 --> 00:49.281
(LAUGHING) Oh, come on.

00:49.283 --> 00:51.650
That's a funny joke.

00:52.519 --> 00:53.786
Told you.

00:53.788 --> 00:55.087
She'll be back.

00:55.089 --> 00:59.425
<i>OLDER TED: And we didn't</i>
<i>see Lily for four weeks.</i>

01:12.539 --> 01:14.073
<i>OLDER TED: Kids,</i>
<i>after getting laid off,</i>

01:14.075 --> 01:16.475
<i>I was</i>
<i>finally pursuing</i>
<i>my lifelong dream,</i>

01:16.477 --> 01:18.377
<i>starting my own</i>
<i>architecture firm.</i>

01:18.379 --> 01:19.945
<i>All I needed</i>
<i>was some clients.</i>

01:19.947 --> 01:23.382
I think it's so great that
you're striking out on
your own, Ted.

01:23.384 --> 01:24.950
I admire that.
Thanks.

01:24.952 --> 01:27.386
And thanks for being so cool
with me using the apartment.

01:27.388 --> 01:29.788
Oh,
yeah, of course.
Anything you need.

01:29.790 --> 01:30.756
<i>(CHEERING ON TV)</i>

01:30.758 --> 01:34.393
Hey, small thing, do you mind
not watching television
during business hours?

01:34.395 --> 01:35.527
This isn't working!

01:35.529 --> 01:37.896
I'm sorry. It's just,
I can't concentrate
while<i> Wheel of Fortune </i> is...

01:37.898 --> 01:38.964
<i>(WHEEL DINGS)</i>

01:38.966 --> 01:41.300
A penny saved is
a Penny Marshall!
Yes!

01:41.302 --> 01:44.470
Ted, I know you're nervous,
but you've got to stop
procrastinating.

01:44.472 --> 01:49.608
You've spent the last two days
choosing the official pen of
Mosbius Designs.

01:49.610 --> 01:55.314
Hey, I've made
some progress, huh?
I've eliminated felt-tip.

01:55.316 --> 01:58.851
Who am I kidding?
Felt's back in
the ball game.

01:59.519 --> 02:02.421
Hey. You hear there's
gonna be more layoffs?

02:02.423 --> 02:04.623
I know.
I'm freaking out.

02:04.625 --> 02:06.525
Are you worried?
Are you kidding?

02:06.527 --> 02:09.828
The things I know
about this company,
I won't ever be fired.

02:09.830 --> 02:12.331
I mean,
there's a pretty good chance
one day I'll wash up on shore

02:12.333 --> 02:15.734
with no fingerprints or
teeth, but I won't be
fired.

02:15.736 --> 02:17.870
Well,
I wish I had
your confidence.

02:17.872 --> 02:21.507
Look,
you just need a way to make
yourself absolutely essential.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.675
Well, I work harder
than anyone in my
division.

02:23.677 --> 02:27.412
Yeah. Keeping your job has
nothing to do with hard work.

02:27.414 --> 02:28.881
You need a thing.
What do you mean, a thing?

02:28.883 --> 02:32.351
You know, something
that makes you fun
and well-liked,

02:32.353 --> 02:33.619
like Marcus Denisco.

02:33.621 --> 02:35.954
<i>OLDER TED: Marcus Denisco</i>
<i>worked in Account Services</i>

02:35.956 --> 02:38.957
<i>and was perhaps</i>
<i>the most expendable</i>
<i>employee at the company.</i>

02:38.959 --> 02:41.727
I brought some donuts.
They're probably stupid.

02:41.729 --> 02:44.530
<i>OLDER TED: But eventually,</i>
<i>he came to be known as...</i>

02:44.532 --> 02:45.697
Food Guy!
Food Guy!

02:45.699 --> 02:48.367
Who wants some pulled pork?
Of course you do! Come on!

02:48.369 --> 02:49.735
(ALL CHEERING)

02:49.737 --> 02:52.571
I love Food Guy.
They could never lay him off.

02:52.573 --> 02:54.840
Mmm-hmm.
You know what I
love about Food Guy?

02:54.842 --> 02:57.442
He always has food.
He always has food.

02:57.444 --> 02:58.744
See? That's what you need.

02:58.746 --> 03:01.380
You need that thing
that makes you a guy.

03:01.382 --> 03:07.286
Oh, I have that
thing that makes me a guy.
Maybe even a guy and a half.

03:07.288 --> 03:08.353
Not that thing.

03:08.355 --> 03:11.323
You know, a thing.
Like Toy Guy.

03:11.325 --> 03:12.357
Guys, bad news.

03:12.359 --> 03:17.696
As your HR rep, I gotta review
the new overtime scheduling
policy with you.

03:17.698 --> 03:22.868
The good news is
we're gonna do it while
wearing Wolverine claws!

03:22.870 --> 03:24.403
(CHEERING)

03:24.405 --> 03:28.907
Section 5A,
overtime will no longer
be paid at time and a half.

03:28.909 --> 03:30.876
This is awesome!
Claw five!

03:30.878 --> 03:32.544
(WHOOPING)

03:32.845 --> 03:34.546
I love Toy Guy.

03:34.548 --> 03:35.847
See? You need a thing.

03:35.849 --> 03:37.849
Like YouTube Clip Guy.

03:37.851 --> 03:39.051
<i>(BABY CRYING)</i>

03:39.053 --> 03:40.919
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

03:45.024 --> 03:48.760
You're right.
I do need a thing.

03:48.762 --> 03:50.095
But choose wisely.

03:50.097 --> 03:52.698
You
don't want to be
Creepy Back Rub Guy.

03:52.700 --> 03:54.032
Hey, don't fill up.

03:54.034 --> 03:55.701
Food Guy's got
Panna Cotta in
his office.

03:55.703 --> 03:56.735
Ooh!

03:58.071 --> 03:59.972
DOUGLAS: Hey, buddy.

04:00.540 --> 04:02.874
Hey, Douglas.

04:02.876 --> 04:07.179
Wow. You're so tight.

04:07.181 --> 04:10.716
I was
relaxed about
two seconds ago.

04:12.485 --> 04:14.419
You're next.

04:15.955 --> 04:18.423
Hi.
Welcome to
Mosbius Designs.

04:18.425 --> 04:20.559
(SIGHS)
Who the hell are you?

04:20.561 --> 04:23.528
I'm PJ,
Mr. Mosby's assistant.

04:23.530 --> 04:24.830
Ted,
what the hell is going...
I'm sorry,

04:24.832 --> 04:27.966
we do not interrupt Mr. Mosby
during his brainstorming hour.

04:27.968 --> 04:29.134
(INTERCOM BEEPING)

04:29.136 --> 04:31.770
<i>It's okay, PJ.</i>
<i>That's Robin.</i>
<i>She lives here.</i>

04:31.772 --> 04:36.608
<i>Oh, I'm sorry</i>
<i>for the disturbance, sir.</i>
<i>Do you need anything else?</i>

04:36.610 --> 04:38.477
<i>Well, I wouldn't</i>
<i>say no to a cup of...</i>

04:38.479 --> 04:40.512
You're right there!

04:40.514 --> 04:44.449
So now Ted has an assistant
to help him not do anything.

04:44.451 --> 04:46.518
Hey, PJ's been
a huge help to
me,

04:46.520 --> 04:48.954
setting up the office,
designing the web site.

04:48.956 --> 04:51.823
And in return,
I'm mentoring a
bright, young mind.

04:51.825 --> 04:54.259
Ah, yes, the mentoring.

04:54.261 --> 04:57.029
I want you to go
outside today
and simply

04:57.031 --> 05:00.499
put your hands on
buildings. All right?

05:00.501 --> 05:04.603
Feel the concrete pulse.
Listen.

05:04.605 --> 05:09.007
Listen to the stories
the stones are telling you.

05:09.776 --> 05:11.743
And pick up
my dry cleaning.

05:11.745 --> 05:13.011
I will.

05:13.013 --> 05:16.648
Thank you so much, Mr. Mosby.
All right.

05:17.717 --> 05:18.750
Hey, Ted?

05:18.752 --> 05:20.018
(DOOR CLOSES)

05:20.020 --> 05:22.921
This table
just told me
you're a douche.

05:23.990 --> 05:25.857
This whole mentoring
thing is just another way

05:25.859 --> 05:28.160
to procrastinate from
actually calling clients.

05:28.162 --> 05:31.096
I'm not procrastinating.
I just...

05:31.098 --> 05:32.831
I want everything
to be perfect, okay?

05:32.833 --> 05:34.199
I only get
one shot at this.

05:34.201 --> 05:36.535
Fine, but PJ
is not helping.

05:36.537 --> 05:37.202
Hey, hey.

05:37.204 --> 05:40.572
If Ted says that PJ is
important to the company,

05:40.574 --> 05:42.741
then PJ is not
going anywhere.

05:42.743 --> 05:44.743
See? He's very valuable.

05:44.745 --> 05:46.678
Whoa, whoa.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.946
PJ's a guy?

05:47.948 --> 05:50.015
PJ's not some hot
chick you're banging?

05:50.017 --> 05:52.417
No, I'm mentoring him.

05:52.419 --> 05:53.852
(GROANING IN DISGUST)

05:53.854 --> 05:55.220
Mentoring.

05:55.222 --> 05:59.458
I mentored
a young fellow once.
Even made him my wingman.

05:59.460 --> 06:02.027
Then, one day,
he hired an assistant

06:02.029 --> 06:04.830
to work 10 feet
from his bedroom

06:04.832 --> 06:08.166
who, get this,
isn't a hot chick,

06:08.168 --> 06:10.435
proving he
never listened
to a word I said.

06:10.437 --> 06:13.572
And do you know
that young man's name?

06:13.574 --> 06:14.906
Ted Mosby?

06:14.908 --> 06:16.074
Maybe.

06:16.076 --> 06:17.743
I don't remember.

06:17.745 --> 06:20.445
Because he is dead to me!

06:23.883 --> 06:27.886
PJ's gonna be getting
a very confusing card
in the mail

06:27.888 --> 06:31.089
along with a garment
that he should by
no means

06:31.091 --> 06:34.726
wear for three days
and then mail back
to me.

06:37.830 --> 06:38.730
Hey, Barney.

06:38.732 --> 06:41.633
I thought
of a thing to make
me more essential here.

06:41.635 --> 06:45.837
I'm Eco Guy, 'cause everybody
loves a guy who recycles,
right?

06:45.839 --> 06:47.706
Fired. What else you got?

06:47.708 --> 06:50.542
I thought of a few
others. Wacky Tie Guy.

06:50.544 --> 06:51.243
Fired.

06:51.245 --> 06:52.844
Daily Fun Fact Guy?

06:52.846 --> 06:54.713
Did you know
that you're fired?

06:54.715 --> 06:57.048
I Know a Good
Stretch for That Guy?

06:57.050 --> 06:58.850
Downward-facing fired.

06:58.852 --> 06:59.918
Monty Python Guy?

06:59.920 --> 07:03.755
(IMITATING KNIGHTS) We are
the knights who say,
"You're fired."

07:03.757 --> 07:06.558
Wait! Wait! I did
use to run a fantasy

07:06.560 --> 07:08.493
baseball league
back in law school.

07:08.495 --> 07:10.962
That's not bad.
You might be onto something.

07:10.964 --> 07:13.999
Awesome. Awesome!
I'll be Fantasy Guy!

07:14.001 --> 07:17.068
We'll have
to make you Sports Guy.
We already have a Fantasy Guy.

07:17.070 --> 07:19.638
What's up, bros?
Hey, Frank.

07:20.673 --> 07:21.640
(WHIRRING)

07:21.642 --> 07:23.175
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

07:24.577 --> 07:25.777
Hello?

07:25.779 --> 07:29.815
Hey, PJ.
Where are you?
You're never late.

07:29.817 --> 07:32.984
You're on top of
the Empire State
Building?

07:32.986 --> 07:34.152
(LAUGHS)

07:34.154 --> 07:37.556
Listen to the old gal.
She's got some stories
to tell.

07:37.558 --> 07:40.926
Take
all the time
you need. Okay.

07:42.895 --> 07:46.531
Wait a second.
"Ted Mosby Home."

07:47.600 --> 07:51.536
Oh, my God,
the call's coming
from inside the house.

07:59.912 --> 08:04.015
That's not the
Empire State Building.

08:08.754 --> 08:11.790
Robin,
you cannot sleep
with my assistant.

08:11.792 --> 08:15.193
I'm trying to
run a business here.
How did this even happen?

08:15.195 --> 08:18.663
Well,
at lunch, when you
go on your wisdom walks,

08:18.665 --> 08:21.766
it gives me and PJ
some time alone together.

08:21.768 --> 08:24.970
Inspiration,
do your thing.

08:24.972 --> 08:28.807
It always does, sir.
It always does.

08:30.343 --> 08:34.779
Hey, PJ, I actually have an
architectural question for
you.

08:34.781 --> 08:36.314
How does Ted's ass taste?

08:36.316 --> 08:41.653
I wouldn't know, but I
assume it tastes like
genius.

08:43.990 --> 08:45.257
(SIGHING)

08:45.259 --> 08:46.191
(RATTLING)

08:46.193 --> 08:47.292
Why is the bathroom locked?

08:47.294 --> 08:50.095
Visitors
need to sign in
for the bathroom key.

08:50.097 --> 08:55.233
Listen, Peej, and I want you
to think this over real good
before you answer.

08:55.235 --> 08:59.771
Are you
telling me that I can't go to
the bathroom in my apartment?

08:59.773 --> 09:02.007
No. I am telling you

09:02.009 --> 09:04.075
that you need
to ask permission

09:04.077 --> 09:07.612
to use
the bathroom
in my office.

09:07.614 --> 09:09.781
Why is that so hot?

09:10.616 --> 09:13.118
Robin,
there are billions
of guys in the world.

09:13.120 --> 09:14.786
Why do you have to
sleep with my assistant?

09:14.788 --> 09:17.756
Ted, when I get off work,
it's 5:30 in the morning.

09:17.758 --> 09:20.725
Do you have any idea
what kind of guys
I'm meeting?

09:20.727 --> 09:22.327
I deliver newspapers.

09:22.329 --> 09:25.330
It's a dirty job,
but somebody's
got to do it.

09:25.332 --> 09:26.097
(LAUGHING)

09:26.099 --> 09:30.969
Don't worry. I'll wash them
before I handle your business.

09:30.971 --> 09:31.937
I live with my mom.

09:31.939 --> 09:37.242
At night,
we watch TV in her bed.
We call it Cuddle Club.

09:37.244 --> 09:42.247
So, you get up
really early to trade on
the European stock exchanges.

09:42.249 --> 09:43.348
What's that like?

09:43.350 --> 09:46.484
Look,
is this gonna
happen or not?

09:46.486 --> 09:49.054
Okay, first of all,
I've hung out with
Fantasy Guy.

09:49.056 --> 09:53.091
You could do a lot worse.
Secondly, this has to stop.

09:53.093 --> 09:55.226
Distracting PJ is going
to kill our productivity.

09:55.228 --> 09:56.828
(SCOFFS) What productivity?

09:56.830 --> 09:58.797
You haven't even
called a single
client.

09:58.799 --> 10:02.167
Hey, once
I get the website up,
the brochures printed,

10:02.169 --> 10:04.102
and figure out
what trust games
we're going to play

10:04.104 --> 10:07.872
at the
corporate retreat,
I am making those calls.

10:07.874 --> 10:09.140
Corporate retreat?

10:09.142 --> 10:12.777
Mr. Mosby and I are
going camping on
the roof.

10:14.380 --> 10:15.413
Hey, Sports Guy.

10:15.415 --> 10:16.815
I hear
people are raving
about your league.

10:16.817 --> 10:19.317
It's a lot harder than
I thought it would be.

10:19.319 --> 10:21.786
Between entry fees
and transaction fees

10:21.788 --> 10:23.822
and penalty fees,
I'm actually...

10:23.824 --> 10:25.857
I'm holding on
to a lot of money.

10:25.859 --> 10:29.260
Great work, Sports Guy.
That's for last week.

10:33.065 --> 10:36.801
<i>MARSHALL: ...60, 80, 100.</i>

10:36.803 --> 10:40.939
<i>Okay. This is $18,000 cash.</i>

10:40.941 --> 10:42.007
<i>It's not a big deal.</i>

10:42.009 --> 10:45.176
<i>I'll just take it home</i>
<i>and put it somewhere safe.</i>

10:45.178 --> 10:49.481
<i>Okay,</i>
<i>just walking down the street</i>
<i>with some money in my pocket.</i>

10:49.483 --> 10:51.282
<i>Don't touch the money.</i>

10:51.284 --> 10:53.985
<i>That's</i>
<i>so obvious.</i>
<i>Just be cool.</i>

10:53.987 --> 10:56.755
<i>Oh, no.</i>
<i>The baby's onto me.</i>

10:56.757 --> 10:59.758
<i>Babies</i>
<i>can smell money.</i>
<i>Everyone knows that!</i>

10:59.760 --> 11:02.861
I'm carrying
a lot of money!

11:02.863 --> 11:06.531
Seriously, dude, I'm not sure
how much longer I can keep
doing this.

11:06.533 --> 11:11.002
Marshall, last week you
were trash that no one
wanted to look at.

11:11.004 --> 11:12.504
Now, you're Sports Guy.

11:12.506 --> 11:15.306
I was trash?
Last week!

11:15.308 --> 11:18.977
Hey,
there's Ted Mosby
of Mosbius Designs.

11:18.979 --> 11:20.178
How's the home
office coming,
buddy?

11:20.180 --> 11:25.083
Well, it was going great till
Robin started banging my
assistant.

11:25.085 --> 11:26.818
(EXCLAIMING)

11:26.820 --> 11:28.753
Ted, it's our apartment,
okay?

11:28.755 --> 11:30.555
You leave
a big chocolate
cake on the counter,

11:30.557 --> 11:33.291
Mama's gonna cut her off
a slice.

11:33.293 --> 11:34.325
I told you.

11:34.327 --> 11:36.828
Hire a cute assistant
that you can sleep with,

11:36.830 --> 11:39.230
but instead you
hire a cute assistant
that Robin can sleep with.

11:39.232 --> 11:41.499
And of course
he's gonna sleep with
her, Ted. Look at her!

11:41.501 --> 11:43.902
She's the greatest
woman on the planet!

11:43.904 --> 11:45.136
I'm getting off topic!

11:45.138 --> 11:45.570
You're an idiot!

11:45.572 --> 11:48.673
That's
my message!
You're an idiot!

11:51.110 --> 11:51.943
No.

11:51.945 --> 11:57.082
One person
storming off isn't enough!
Marshall, storm off with me!

12:00.953 --> 12:03.888
Barney.
Dude, why are
you this upset

12:03.890 --> 12:06.524
about Ted not having sex
with the people he hires?

12:06.526 --> 12:08.660
Because it hurts!

12:08.662 --> 12:10.061
It hurts you how?

12:10.063 --> 12:13.598
It hurts because I love

12:13.600 --> 12:14.833
Ted

12:15.201 --> 12:17.168
having sex with women.

12:17.170 --> 12:18.903
I'm a very dedicated wingman!

12:18.905 --> 12:21.473
Look, Lily's the only person
that I can talk to about
this stuff.

12:21.475 --> 12:22.741
Just get her to talk to me.

12:22.743 --> 12:24.809
I'll try, but look,
there's no guarantees.

12:24.811 --> 12:29.013
She's still really
outraged about that joke.

12:29.015 --> 12:31.149
(SIGHING) That joke!

12:31.151 --> 12:35.920
Tore our little group apart,
pitted people I love against
each other.

12:35.922 --> 12:37.122
Seriously, I wish...

12:37.124 --> 12:41.659
I wish that joke had
never come into our lives.

12:41.661 --> 12:42.994
(LAUGHING)

12:42.996 --> 12:44.462
It's kind of
funny though,
right?

12:44.464 --> 12:45.830
It's so funny, man.

12:47.032 --> 12:48.500
Hey, good news, PJ.

12:48.502 --> 12:50.502
The brochures you
designed just came in.

12:50.504 --> 12:51.703
Really interesting
choice for the cover.

12:51.705 --> 12:56.241
I like how instead of one of
my designs, you chose this.

12:56.243 --> 13:00.512
You know what? I must've
sent in the wrong photo.

13:00.514 --> 13:01.646
You think?

13:01.648 --> 13:04.749
Look, PJ,
the website's
still not done.

13:04.751 --> 13:07.252
You didn't even show up
to the corporate retreat.

13:07.254 --> 13:10.255
By the way,
I saw a shooting star,

13:10.257 --> 13:12.123
and you're late every day!

13:12.125 --> 13:14.926
I'm sorry, PJ.
I gotta get focused.

13:14.928 --> 13:15.960
You're fired.

13:15.962 --> 13:17.829
You can't fire...

13:17.831 --> 13:19.564
PJ, you're fired.

13:19.566 --> 13:20.865
Fine!

13:23.836 --> 13:28.039
Hey, baby.
I just got fired.

13:28.041 --> 13:29.874
Yeah,
I'll wait for
you at your place.

13:29.876 --> 13:31.643
Okay, bye.

13:32.011 --> 13:33.144
<i>(CHEERING ON TV)</i>

13:33.146 --> 13:36.014
Oh!<i> Wheel of Fortune.</i>

13:40.319 --> 13:44.022
I love having all this
free time to spend
with you.

13:44.024 --> 13:46.858
I'm going to kiss
you here and here.

13:46.860 --> 13:47.959
Ooh! Ooh!

13:47.961 --> 13:51.095
And here and here. And...

13:51.097 --> 13:52.697
Oh!
Please stop.

13:54.300 --> 13:55.900
I'm going to go
to the bathroom.

13:55.902 --> 13:57.669
I'll miss you.

13:57.671 --> 13:59.637
I'll miss you, too.

14:03.809 --> 14:05.710
You're already sick
of him, aren't you?

14:05.712 --> 14:07.245
He's driving me crazy.

14:07.247 --> 14:09.747
When PJ had a job,
he was sexy.

14:09.749 --> 14:11.850
He was guardian
of the bathroom key.

14:11.852 --> 14:16.921
A hot guy
telling you when
you can and can't pee?

14:16.923 --> 14:18.756
(SIGHS) That's the dream.

14:18.758 --> 14:21.593
That's the dream? The dream?

14:21.595 --> 14:23.862
Like what Martin Luther King
was talking about?

14:23.864 --> 14:27.799
I have
to end it, don't I?
I'm terrible at breakups.

14:27.801 --> 14:29.334
I still have to
go a little bit,

14:29.336 --> 14:31.102
but I couldn't
be away from you
one second longer.

14:31.104 --> 14:33.705
Oh! Listen.

14:34.940 --> 14:37.041
Dude, I don't know.
What?

14:37.043 --> 14:39.244
Yeah, it's just...

14:39.246 --> 14:41.813
It's not really...

14:41.815 --> 14:43.982
Ix-nay, you know?

14:43.984 --> 14:46.918
Ix-nay on what?

14:46.920 --> 14:47.886
Not feeling it.

14:47.888 --> 14:49.654
Not feeling what?

14:49.656 --> 14:50.955
But friends and stuff?

14:50.957 --> 14:54.158
Oh, my God, this is
the worst breakup ever.

14:54.160 --> 14:55.860
You're breaking up with me?

14:55.862 --> 15:00.398
If that's
what you want,
I totally understand.

15:00.400 --> 15:05.136
Hey, you still haven't
activated that shortstop
the Mariners just brought up.

15:05.138 --> 15:06.938
Gotta have it. Ha!

15:06.940 --> 15:07.839
(LAUGHING)

15:07.841 --> 15:09.941
See, Sports Guy?
People love you.

15:09.943 --> 15:12.076
I can't be Sports
Guy anymore, okay?

15:12.078 --> 15:13.044
It's killing me!

15:13.046 --> 15:14.879
I keep getting
these constant
texts

15:14.881 --> 15:17.882
and e-mails and phone calls
in the middle of the night.

15:17.884 --> 15:22.787
(SOFTLY)
Sometimes I even think
that I'm being followed.

15:22.789 --> 15:24.055
Hey, buddy.

15:24.057 --> 15:25.924
I need you to push
that trade through,

15:25.926 --> 15:27.725
so I can set up my new lineup.

15:27.727 --> 15:31.296
Wow,
you really carry it in
your shoulders, don't you?

15:31.298 --> 15:33.765
Seriously, it's over.

15:33.767 --> 15:35.967
Do you want me to stop?

15:37.036 --> 15:38.836
No.

15:38.838 --> 15:41.039
<i>OLDER TED: With Robin and PJ</i>
<i>broken up, I was free to make</i>

15:41.041 --> 15:44.075
<i>some staffing</i>
<i>changes in the office.</i>

15:45.177 --> 15:46.744
Hi,
welcome to
Mosbius Designs.

15:46.746 --> 15:49.547
(SIGHS) You got
to be kidding me.

15:49.549 --> 15:52.650
<i>OLDER TED: And now that</i>
<i>PJ was back at work...</i>

15:53.886 --> 15:56.321
You got to be kidding me.

15:56.323 --> 16:00.124
So, apparently Robin
and PJ are an item again.

16:00.126 --> 16:02.660
You got to be kidding me!

16:04.697 --> 16:05.697
(COUGHING)

16:05.699 --> 16:07.031
Are you all right?

16:07.033 --> 16:07.899
(SIGHING)

16:07.901 --> 16:09.300
Okay, since Lily's
not talking to me,

16:09.302 --> 16:11.035
there's something
that I have to tell you.

16:11.037 --> 16:14.072
And this isn't easy
to say, all right?

16:14.840 --> 16:17.675
I'm... Wait for it.

16:17.677 --> 16:20.211
...in... Wait for it.

16:20.213 --> 16:23.181
...love... Wait for it.

16:23.183 --> 16:25.783
...with... Wait for it.

16:27.186 --> 16:28.720
(SIGHING)

16:30.255 --> 16:32.991
...a... Wait for it.

16:32.993 --> 16:33.958
...certain...
Wait for it.

16:33.960 --> 16:35.727
I know that you're
in love with Robin!

16:35.729 --> 16:36.928
What?

16:36.930 --> 16:39.764
Lily told me.
She told you?

16:39.766 --> 16:40.965
Great.

16:40.967 --> 16:41.299
(SCOFFS)

16:41.301 --> 16:45.937
I bet you guys
have been laughing at me
behind my back the whole time.

16:45.939 --> 16:51.909
Actually, in a weird way,
we both think you're kind
of perfect for each other.

16:51.911 --> 16:52.977
You do?

16:52.979 --> 16:55.680
Yeah. Matter of fact,
we even try to sit on
the same side of the booth

16:55.682 --> 16:57.348
so you two will
have to sit together.

16:57.350 --> 16:59.250
Really? That's so sweet.

16:59.252 --> 17:04.822
But let's be clear.
I don't love her.
Okay?

17:04.824 --> 17:07.258
I just miss her
when she's not around.

17:07.260 --> 17:09.427
I think
about her all the time,
and I imagine us one day

17:09.429 --> 17:11.062
running towards each
other in slow motion,

17:11.064 --> 17:13.898
and I'm wearing
a brown suede vest.

17:13.900 --> 17:15.500
Are you ever going to
tell her how you feel?

17:15.502 --> 17:19.103
No. Maybe.
Never. I don't know. Look...

17:19.105 --> 17:19.971
(EXCLAIMS)

17:19.973 --> 17:23.107
I just need to get that
PJ idiot away from her.

17:23.109 --> 17:27.311
If Lily were here, she'd know
exactly how to get rid of him.

17:27.313 --> 17:28.279
Maybe I can help.

17:28.281 --> 17:30.048
Marshall, you're no Lily.

17:30.050 --> 17:34.018
Lily is a diabolical
puppet master, subtly
manipulating every situation

17:34.020 --> 17:39.257
to get
exactly what she wants.
She's pure evil, Marshall.

17:39.259 --> 17:42.360
You got a good one there.
Hang on to her.

17:42.362 --> 17:46.597
<i>OLDER TED: Meanwhile,</i>
<i>my bizarre tug of war</i>
<i>with Robin over PJ continued.</i>

17:46.599 --> 17:51.235
Hey, PJ.
I was about to go
on my wisdom walk.

17:51.237 --> 17:52.837
Want to join me?

17:52.839 --> 17:56.741
Hey, PJ. I took
the bathroom key
without asking.

17:56.743 --> 17:58.443
What
are you going
to do about it?

17:58.445 --> 17:59.277
(SIGHING)

17:59.279 --> 18:01.512
Look, you guys
are both great,

18:01.514 --> 18:05.316
but the truth is
I'm taking another job.

18:05.318 --> 18:06.084
These are for you.

18:06.086 --> 18:09.287
Robin,
I hope this letter
offers some closure.

18:09.289 --> 18:12.857
Ted, I'm really
going to miss you.

18:14.593 --> 18:17.128
You can't
trade Manny Ramirez
for two middle relievers!

18:17.130 --> 18:19.063
If you veto that trade,
I am out of the league!

18:19.065 --> 18:22.233
Okay! Okay!
I'll figure it out.

18:24.336 --> 18:26.971
Hire the kid to be
a paralegal.

18:26.973 --> 18:30.541
He gets to do all the work,
and you still get to be
Sports Guy.

18:30.543 --> 18:34.412
Pure evil, Eriksen.
Pure evil.

18:36.415 --> 18:38.749
Hey, thanks.

18:42.488 --> 18:45.089
Hey. You okay?

18:47.292 --> 18:50.161
What if I don't
think of the books?

18:50.163 --> 18:51.295
Excuse me?

18:51.297 --> 18:52.697
There's this famous
architecture story

18:52.699 --> 18:56.200
about an architect
who designed this
library.

18:56.202 --> 18:57.835
It was perfect.

18:57.837 --> 19:00.004
But every year,
the whole thing would

19:00.006 --> 19:03.274
sink a couple of
inches into the ground.

19:03.276 --> 19:05.910
Eventually,
the building
was condemned.

19:05.912 --> 19:11.182
He forgot to account
for the weight of
the books.

19:11.184 --> 19:15.453
This company,
it's just me.

19:15.455 --> 19:18.156
What if I don't
think of the books?

19:18.158 --> 19:20.825
Okay, first of all,
nobody goes to libraries

19:20.827 --> 19:22.560
anymore,
so who cares
about that guy?

19:22.562 --> 19:27.331
Secondly, you
need to get on the phone
and start calling clients.

19:27.333 --> 19:29.100
The longer I put off
starting my own firm,

19:29.102 --> 19:34.639
the longer it can
remain a dream and not
something I screwed up at.

19:34.641 --> 19:37.975
I mean,
it's like I'm giving
up before I even started.

19:37.977 --> 19:40.011
You want to talk
about giving up?

19:40.013 --> 19:42.480
I used
to describe
my ideal guy as

19:42.482 --> 19:45.416
funny, smart,
passionate, challenging.

19:45.418 --> 19:50.521
And now, apparently, I will
settle for "in my apartment."

19:50.523 --> 19:53.357
I mean, didn't you think you'd
have it all more figured out
by now?

19:53.359 --> 19:57.061
Are you kidding?
By 30, I was going to
be annoyingly successful,

19:57.063 --> 20:00.131
married to
the perfect woman,
maybe a kid on the way.

20:00.133 --> 20:03.434
Instead,
I'm just some guy
sitting in his apartment

20:03.436 --> 20:07.305
having a staring
contest with his
phone.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.173
And losing.

20:09.608 --> 20:13.077
Hey. You can take that thing.

20:16.949 --> 20:18.282
(SIGHS)

20:29.661 --> 20:31.963
Hi, this is
Ted Mosby of
Mosbius Designs.

20:31.965 --> 20:36.167
I'm calling to inquire about
any design needs you may have
now or in the future.

20:36.169 --> 20:37.168
That sounds great, buddy.

20:37.170 --> 20:38.436
Really? I sound confident?
Yup.

20:38.438 --> 20:39.937
Now call an actual client.

20:39.939 --> 20:41.305
Great.

20:45.944 --> 20:47.445
Hey, Food Guy!

20:48.547 --> 20:50.848
Hey, Toy Guy!

20:55.554 --> 20:57.255
Who's that guy?

20:58.290 --> 21:00.091
He doesn't work here.

21:00.093 --> 21:02.360
I think we should
leave the building.

21:02.362 --> 21:02.793
Really?

21:02.795 --> 21:05.863
This has happened before.
